Tests on original dataset

adf.test(tesla_ts)
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  tesla_ts
## Dickey-Fuller = -0.95717, Lag order = 13, p-value = 0.9457
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
kpss.test(tesla_ts)
## Warning in kpss.test(tesla_ts): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  KPSS Test for Level Stationarity
## 
## data:  tesla_ts
## KPSS Level = 12.707, Truncation lag parameter = 9, p-value = 0.01

KPSS test: null hypothesis: TS is stationary. p-value of KPSS test is small enough to reject the null hypothesis, therefore, not stationary.

ADF test: null hypothesis: TS is not stationary. p-value of ADF test is larger than 0.05, therefore, we cannot reject the null hypothesis. not stationary.
